<item>
            <title>[HIVE-5496] hcat -e &quot;drop database if exists&quot; fails on authorizing non-existent null db</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-5496</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running a &quot;drop database if exists&quot; call on hcat commandline, it fails authorization with a NPE because it tries to authorize access to a null database. This should be changed to not call authorize if the db for the DropDatabaseDesc is null.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
